President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring November 24 through November 30, 2019, as National Family Week. In the proclamation, he highlights the importance of family bonds in shaping values, character, and the development of productive citizens. The proclamation also mentions the administration's efforts in empowering families through economic policies such as tax cuts, job creation, and support for child care affordability. It also mentions criminal justice reform efforts aimed at maintaining family and community ties for successful prisoner reentry. The proclamation calls for communities, churches, and individuals to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor and strengthen families.